                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7415</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Mr. <persName type="to">Parker</persName>, representing American interests
                        in Mexico</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-16T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1916, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>280. Your 267, March 13, 8 p.m. Practically all reports from American consular
                    officers in Mexico encouraging. Department does not anticipate that withdrawal
                    will be necessary, but should necessity arise you are instructed to entrust
                    representation American interests, Embassy and consular property to British or
                    French representative.</p>
                <p>Department’s March 11, 11 p.m., and March 14, 8 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d975fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">See</hi> Political Affairs, <ref target="#pg_490">p.
                            490</ref>.</note>, should be consulted for your guidance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
